"43:86:13" : {s: 43, a: 86, w: 13, r: "علم", t: "يَعْلَمُونَ", l: "عَلِمَ", lc: 382, tl: "yaʿlamūna", lb: "(সে) জানে",e: "know", b: "তারা জানে", i: "mereka mengetahui", f: 81, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows.", ag: "فعل مضارع وضمير متصل ", eg: "Verb Imperfect and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPF", qual: "", deg: "3", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَعْلَمُ،عَلِمَ،عَلِيمٌۢ"},
